{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox magazine | title = Gatra | logo = | logo_size = | image_file = Gatra Cover.jpg | image_alt = Red magazine cover depicting toy boat in stylized sea made of dragons, with GATRA printed in large letters across the top | image_caption = February 2012 cover | editor = | editor_title = | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | photographer = | category = News and politics | frequency = Weekly | circulation = | publisher = Era Media Informasi | founder = | founded = {{Start date and age|1994}} | firstdate = <!-- {{Start date|year|month|day}} --> | company = | country = [[Indonesia]] | based = [[Jakarta]] | language = [[Bahasa Indonesia]] | website = {{URL|gatra.com}} | issn = | oclc = }}
'''''Gatra''''' is a weekly [[news magazine]] published in [[Jakarta]], [[Indonesia]]. It is one of the two principal news magazines in the country, the other being [[Tempo (Indonesian magazine)|''Tempo'']].<ref>Kuipers, Joel C. "The Media". In [http://lcweb2.loc.gov/frd/cs/pdf/CS_Indonesia.pdf ''Indonesia: A Country Study''] (William H. Frederick and Robert L. Worden, eds.). [[Library of Congress]] [[Federal Research Division]] (2011).</ref>
''Gatra'' was founded in 1994. The magazine has its headquarters in Jakarta.<ref>{{cite book|author=Matt Davies|title=Indonesia's War Over Aceh: Last Stand on Mecca's Porch|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ppx-AgAAQBAJ&pg=PA127|accessdate=21 March 2015|date=27 September 2006|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-134-19331-8|page=127}}</ref><ref name="efc">{{cite book|author=Elizabeth Fuller Collins|title=Indonesia Betrayed: How Development Fails|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ojOtXYruFTwC&pg=PA235|accessdate=21 March 2015|year=2007|publisher=University of Hawaii Press|isbn=978-0-8248-3183-7|page=235}}</ref> It provides articles on news and is published on a weekly basis.<ref name=efc/>
