{{Infobox Film Festival | name = Hong Kong Jewish Film Festival | image = Hong_Kong_Jewish_Film_Festival_logo.png | caption = Hong Kong Jewish Film Festival logo | location = [[Hong Kong]] | awards = | founded = 2007 | host = | number = | language = | website = [http://www.hkjff.org/ Hong Kong Jewish Film Festival] }}
The '''Hong Kong Jewish Film Festival''' (HKJFF) is an annual [[film festival]] dedicated to world cinema that focuses on Jewish life, history and culture worldwide. It was founded in 2000 by Howard Elias from [[Toronto]], Canada,<ref name="Sin">{{cite news | url=http://www.timeout.com.hk/film/features/61902/hong-kong-jewish-film-festival.html | title=Hong Kong Jewish Film Festival | work=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out (Hong Kong)]] | date=2 November 2013 | accessdate=1 September 2014 | author=Ben Sin }}</ref> and takes place in [[Hong Kong]].
The 15th Festival ran from 29 November to 7 December 2014. The 16th Festival ran from 14 to 22 November 2015.<ref name="15th Festival">{{cite web | url=http://www.hkjff.org/ | title=The 15th Hong Kong Jewish Film Festival | publisher=Hong Kong Jewish Film Festival | date=2014 | accessdate=1 September 2014}}</ref>
