The '''Island Fringe Festival''' is an independent arts and theatre festival that takes place annually in [[Charlottetown]], [[Prince Edward Island]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Canadian Association of Fringe Festivals|url=http://fringefestivals.com/festival/island-fringe-festival-pei/|website=Island Fringe Festival}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Heald|first1=Melissa|title=O’Leary native to appear in debut production during fringe festival|url=http://www.peicanada.com/west_prince_graphic/article_f50e278e-5360-11e6-9506-83897716397e.html|accessdate=9 January 2017|date=July 27, 2016}}</ref><ref name="CBC News">{{cite news|title=Island Fringe Festival's show goes inside character's mind|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/prince-edward-island/island-fringe-festival-anxiety-nutshell-1.3709762|accessdate=9 January 2017|agency=[[CBC News]]|date=August 5, 2016}}</ref> The Festival was founded by Sarah Segal-Lazar and Megan Stewart<ref name="Montreal Gazette">{{cite news|last1=Brownstein|first1=Bill|title=Bad jews is good start for director, actors; Lisa Rubin worked with a cast of up-and-comers on a sparse budget|url=http://montrealgazette.com/entertainment/theatre/bad-jews-marks-career-debuts-for-two-lead-actors-and-director|accessdate=9 January 2017|agency=Montreal Gazette|date=May 21, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=MacDonald |first1=Mitch |title=River Clyde Pageant being held July 30 and 31 |url=https://www.theguardian.pe.ca/living/2016/7/22/river-clyde-pageant-being-held-july-30-a-4595579.html |accessdate=9 January 2017 |agency=The Guardian |date=July 24, 2016 }}</ref> in 2012<ref name="theguardian.pe.ca">{{cite web|last1=Taweel|first1=Heather|title=Island Fringe Festival coming to Charlottetown|url=http://www.theguardian.pe.ca/living/2015/7/30/island-fringe-festival-coming-to-charlot-4231142.html|agency=The Guardian|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref><ref name="cbc.ca">{{cite web|last1=Gill|first1=Jordan|title=Performers wanted: Island Fringe Festival application deadline approaching|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/prince-edward-island/fringe-festival-applications-coming-1.3919759|website=CBC Prince Edward Island|accessdate=9 January 2017|date=January 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Island Fringe Festival|url=http://www.islandfringe.com/team|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Megan Stewart|url=http://www.riverclydepageant.com/megan-stewart/|website=The River Clyde Pageant|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Fringe Festival - Sarah Segal-Lazar & Cheryl Diell|url=http://www.cbc.ca/mainstreetpei/events/2012/08/24/fringe-festival---sarah-segal-lazar-cheryl-diell/|accessdate=9 January 2017|agency=[[CBC Radio]]|date=August 24, 2012}}</ref> with the first festival taking place in August of that year.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gavin|first1=Jennifer|title=Charlottetown's Art in the Open Festival Set to Begin|url=http://www.city.charlottetown.pe.ca/news.php?id=571|website=City of Charlottetown|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref> The festival is one of three Fringe Festivals in [[Atlantic Canada]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gallant|first1=Vanessa|title=This isn't your typical theatre festival|work=Here|date=August 14, 2014}}</ref> and is a member of the [[Canadian Association of Fringe Festivals]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Canadian Association of Fringe Festivals|url=http://fringefestivals.com/festival/island-fringe-festival-pei/|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref>
==Shows and Venues==
Fringe Performances take place around the city of Charlottetown in conventional and unconventional spaces, such as in homes, on patios, and in bars.<ref name="CBC News"/><ref name="theguardian.pe.ca"/><ref name="cbc.ca"/> All shows in the festival are by donation, with proceeds going directly to artists.<ref name="cbc.ca"/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Taweel|first1=Heather|title=Island Fringe Festival coming to Charlottetown|url=http://www.theguardian.pe.ca/living/2015/7/30/island-fringe-festival-coming-to-charlot-4231142.html|accessdate=9 January 2017|agency=The Guardian|date=July 30, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Island Fringe|url=http://theinspiredcity.com/inspired-projects/38/Island-Fringe|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Island Fringe Festival: 5th Anniversary edition|url=https://www.evensi.ca/the-island-fringe-festival-5th-anniversary-edition-the/181983855|website=Evensi}}</ref> In August 2016, comedian [[Lorne Elliott]] debuted his new work, A Better Play Than Hamlet, at the Island Fringe.<ref>{{cite news|title=Island Fringe Festival presents debut of new Lorne Elliot play|url=http://www.cbc.ca/beta/news/canada/prince-edward-island/lorne-elliot-fringe-festival-p-e-i-1.3707983|accessdate=9 January 2017|agency=[[CBC News]]|date=August 4, 2016}}</ref>
