{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}} {{infobox music festival | music_festival_name = RNB Fridays Live | years_active= 2016–present | location = {{bulleted list|style=font-size: 100%;|NIB Stadium|Eatons Hills Outdoors|Qudos Bank Arena|Titanium Security Arena|Marvel Stadium|Adelaide Showground|Brisbane Showground|Spotless Stadium}} | founders = [[Hits Radio Network]] | dates = October-November | genre = [[Hip Hop music|Hip Hop]], [[R&B]], [[Pop music|Pop]] | website = {{URL|http://rnbfridayslive.com}} }}
'''RNB Friday Live''' is an annual concert series held in [[Australia]]. The series was co-founded by [[Hits Radio Network]] and Frontier Touring in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/usher-joins-other-icons-to-headline-rnb-fridays-live-in-november-20180809-p4zwle.html|title=Usher joins other icons to headline RnB Fridays Live in November|last=Rota|first=Genevieve|date=9 August 2018|website=The Sydney Morning Herald|language=en|access-date=9 November 2018}}</ref> The event features several stages featuring musical artists from many [[Music genre|genres of music]], including [[Rhythm and blues|R&B]], [[Hip hop music|hip hop]], [[electronic dance music]], and pop. The concert series are held in venues across [[Sydney]], [[Melbourne]], [[Brisbane]], [[Adelaide]], and [[Perth]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.frontiertouring.com/rnbfridayslive|title=RNB Fridays Live 2018 Australia Tickets, Concert Dates, Pre-sale & Tour Information {{!}} Frontier Touring Australia & New Zealand|last=Company|first=The Frontier Touring|website=Frontier Touring Australia & New Zealand|language=en|access-date=9 November 2018}}</ref>
